gov.nih.nlm.meme.common
Interface SearchParameter

All Known Implementing Classes:
SearchParameter.Default
public interface SearchParameter

Generically represents a search criterion. Implementations define whether they are single or multiple value searches and whether they are approximate, exact, or range-based searches. Also supported is a generic key/value attribute mechanism for supplying additional needed information not otherwise supported. In practice, this class is used to build SQL queries to search for and build objecst from the database. The various Finder

isRangeSearch

public boolean isRangeSearch()
Returns true if this search parameter is used to find things given a range of identifiers. If this returns true, then getStartId() and getEndId() should return non-null values.

true if this is a range search; false otherwise
